-- U.K. Stocks Drop, led by Barclays, Rio Tinto Group; GlaxoSmithKline Rises
-- David Merritt
-- 2010-07-15T13:49:46Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-07-15/u-k-stocks-drop-led-by-barclays-rio-tinto-group-glaxosmithkline-rises.html

          
          
             U.K. stocks declined, as a fall in
shares of Barclays Plc and Rio Tinto Group overshadowed a rally
in GlaxoSmithKline Plc shares.  
 The benchmark FTSE 100 Index fell 0.5 percent to 5,225.25
at 2:48 p.m. in London, after earlier swinging between gains and
losses.  
          
          


  


        